{"lemma":"حَفْرُ","slug":"حَفْرُ","root":"ح.ف.ر","root_slug":"ح-ف-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ف-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8472","n8477","n8478"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dig, dig out, hollow"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dig or clean a well"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to investigate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lie with"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to emaciate by milking frequently"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَفَرَ (ḥafara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"digging, hollowing"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ḥapar-. Cognate with Biblical Hebrew חָפַר (ḥɔp̄ar, “to dig, search for”).\n\nFrom Proto-Semitic *ḥapr-."},"ipa":["/ħa.fa.ra/","/ħafr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8472","headword_ar":"حَفَرَ","root":"Hfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaforN","text_ar":"حَفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He dug, excavated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hollowed out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the ground, or earth; (KL, PS, &c.;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he cleared out"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing, (K,) as one does the ground; (S, Msb, K;) and a well; (the Lexicons passim;) and a river; (A, Mgh;) with a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miHofaAr","text_ar":"مِحْفَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A;) or with an iron implement; (K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtfr","text_ar":"احتفر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same. (S, A, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hafara","text_ar":"حَفَرَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hafarahu","text_ar":"حَفَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtfrhu","text_ar":"احتفرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He dug for him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(namely, a lizard of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dab~","text_ar":"ضَبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or a jerboa,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to fetch him forth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b2-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He burrowed."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b3-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a torrent)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"furrowed"},{"kind":"text","text":"a valley. (Msb.) [See also 5.] ―         -b4-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Inivit"},{"kind":"text","text":"feminam: (IAar, Msb, K:) the action being likened to that of a man digging a river. (IAar.) ―         -b5- .) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA gayovN laA","text_ar":"هٰذَا غَيْثٌ لَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaHofiruhu A^aHadN","text_ar":"يَحْفِرُهُ اَحَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a rain of which no one knows the utmost extent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hafara varay zayodK","text_ar":"حَفَرَ ثَرَي زَيْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He searched into the affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case, of Zeyd,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and became acquainted with it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b8-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hafara","text_ar":"حَفَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K,) aor. as above, (S,) and so the inf. n., (S, A,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, emaciated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered lean:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a copious flow of milk, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"emaciated"},{"kind":"text","text":"a she-goat: (K, TA:) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a young camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered"},{"kind":"text","text":"his mother"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flabby in flesh by much sucking."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) There is no pregnant animal that pregnancy does not emaciate, except the camel: (S, A:) she fattens in pregnancy. (S.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hafara","text_ar":"حَفَرَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a child)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shed his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawaADiE","text_ar":"رَوَاضِع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"milk-teeth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K, TA.) [See also 4.] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hafarato","text_ar":"حَفَرَتْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawaADiEu Almuhori","text_ar":"رَوَاضِعُ المُهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hufirato","text_ar":"حُفِرَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (accord. to different copies of the A,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The milk-teeth of the colt became in a wabbling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loose, state, previously to their falling out;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because, when they have fallen out, their sockets become hollow. (A.) [See 4.] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hafarati AlA^asonaAnu","text_ar":"حَفَرَتِ الاَسْنَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaforN","text_ar":"حَفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hafirat","text_ar":"حَفِرَت"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafarN","text_ar":"حَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the dial. of BenooAsad, (S, Msb,) and this is the worse of these two forms, (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaforN","text_ar":"حَفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (El-Wá'ee;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hufirat","text_ar":"حُفِرَت"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The teeth became affected with what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaforN","text_ar":"حَفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v. infrà] or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafarN","text_ar":"حَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became unsound:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hafara fuwhu","text_ar":"حَفَرَ فُوهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hafira","text_ar":"حَفِرَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his teeth cankered."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) IDrst says, in the Expos. of the Fs, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hafara","text_ar":"حَفَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hafora fuwhu","text_ar":"حَفْرَ فُوهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is trans.; and that the cause of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hafor","text_ar":"حَفْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the teeth, [or the agent of the verb"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hafara","text_ar":"حَفَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] is old age, or the continuance of a yellow incrustation, [or tartar,] or some kind of canker that effects them: but that the verb in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hafirato sin~uhu","text_ar":"حَفِرَتْ سِنُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafarN","text_ar":"حَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is intrans. (MF.) [The truth probably is, that the former verb is both trans. and intrans., and hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hufirati AlA^asonaAnu","text_ar":"حُفِرَتِ الاَسْنَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and that the latter is intrans. only.] ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hafira","text_ar":"حَفِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, in a bad, corrupt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unsound, state."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","Mgh","IAar","A","S","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n8477","headword_ar":"حَفْرٌ","root":"Hfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafarN","text_ar":"حَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafiyrN","text_ar":"حَفِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Emaciation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leanness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kr.) [See 1.] ―         -b2-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafarN","text_ar":"حَفَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Az, S, Msb, K,) the latter of the dial. of the Benoo-Asad, and the worse of the two forms, (S,) said by IKt to be a bad form, (TA,) and by ISk to be a vulgar mispronunciation, which is attributed to his not having heard the dial. of the Benoo-Asad, (Msb,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A scaling"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulaAq","text_ar":"سُلَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the roots of the teeth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Yaakoob, S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rottenness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an unsound state, of the roots of the teeth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of a scaling of those parts:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what adheres to the teeth, externally and internally:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an erosion of the roots of the teeth by a yellow incrustation between those parts and the gum, externally and internally, pressing upon the bone so that the latter scales away if it be not quickly removed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cankering of the teeth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a yellowness upon the teeth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, IKh, K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaforN","text_ar":"حَفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pimple,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small pustule, in the gum of a child."},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Wá'ee.) [See 1: and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiborN","text_ar":"حِبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["Az","S","Msb","K","TA","Sh","A","IDrd","IKh"]},{"entry_id":"n8478","headword_ar":"حَفَرٌ","root":"Hfr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A well that is widened"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beyond. measure;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaforN","text_ar":"حَفْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafiyrN","text_ar":"حَفِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafyrapN","text_ar":"حَفيرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafyrN","text_ar":"حَفيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth that is taken forth from a hollow, cavity, pit, or the like, that is dug in the ground;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hadamN","text_ar":"هَدَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafiyrapN","text_ar":"حَفِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is dug,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excavated;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadadN","text_ar":"عَدَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabaTN","text_ar":"خَبَطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafaDN","text_ar":"نَفَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the senses of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoduwdN","text_ar":"مَعْدُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxobuwTN","text_ar":"مَخْبُوطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manofuwDN","text_ar":"مَنْفُوضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place that is dug,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like a moat or well;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaforN","text_ar":"حَفْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHofaArN","text_ar":"اَحْفَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) and pl. pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHaAfiyru","text_ar":"اَحَافِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b4-  See, again,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafiyrN","text_ar":"حَفِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b5-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaforN","text_ar":"حَفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","Msb","Az"]}]}}